=head1 NAME

cssh

=head1 VERSION

This document describes cssh version 3.99_01

=head1 USAGE

=head1 DESCRIPTION

THis is a description

=head1 OPTIONAL ARGUMENTS

=over 2

=item -q | --quit | -Q | --QUIT

Enable/Disable automatically quitting after the last client window has
closed (overriding the config file)

=for Euclid:
  false: -Q | --QUIT


=item [identifier]...

List of hosts or cluster tags to open connections to.

Identifiers are either a cluster name or a hostname of the format

  [username@]<hostname>[:<port>]

=cut

=for Euclid:
  identifier.type: /(?:(.*?)@)?(?:[\w\.-]*)(?::(`d+))?

=back

